ENTRY       EC 2.1.1.270                Enzyme
NAME        (+)-6a-hydroxymaackiain 3-O-methyltransferase;
            HM3OMT;
            HMM2
CLASS       Transferases;
            Transferring one-carbon groups;
            Methyltransferases
SYSNAME     S-adenosyl-L-methionine:(+)-6a-hydroxymaackiain 3-O-methyltransferase
REACTION    S-adenosyl-L-methionine + (+)-6a-hydroxymaackiain = S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + (+)-pisatin [RN:R07750]
ALL_REAC    R07750
SUBSTRATE   S-adenosyl-L-methionine [CPD:C00019];
            (+)-6a-hydroxymaackiain [CPD:C16230]
PRODUCT     S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine [CPD:C00021];
            (+)-pisatin [CPD:C10516]
COMMENT     The protein from the plant Pisum sativum (garden pea) methylates (+)-6a-hydroxymaackiain at the 3-position. It also methylates 2,7,4'-trihydroxyisoflavanone on the 4'-position (cf. EC 2.1.1.212, 2,7,4-trihydroxyisoflavanone 4-O-methyltransferase) with lower activity.
